"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"According to an article in the World Economic Forum:\\n\\n\\\"NFT can take many shapes in a virtual world: characters, objects, land, decorative personalization features, such as digital clothing.\\\"\\n\\nIn P2E, players earn the most valuable NFT for their in-game exploits, which they can then sell for real money. This innovation breaks the proprietary, escrow ownership of game assets while preserving security and proof of ownership.\\n\\nIt also leads to the logical conclusion that DeFi is fully compatible with the metadverse.\\n\\nThe World Economic Forum continues:\\n\\nEarn \\\"playing (play) to earn the most potential of the game is that they may create, ownership of digital assets decentralization and exchange market, and when the market and the traditional economy and the potential of legal tender connection is created, allows players to their digital time, energy, and income into the reality of the disposable income of the world.\\\"\\n\\nNaturally, P2E still relies on some form of centralization to limit what is ultimately published as NFT, but there will always be marginal communities that allow anything.\\n\\nOne day, we may reach a point where technology is so thoroughly decentralized and the metasemes so vast that it's almost impossible to police how players present themselves or what business they do there. However, we are far from that reality today.\\n\\nNFT creation is also quickly becoming a commodity, and it is the communities around impressive work that will command the highest valuations and survive the bear market.\\n\\nTraditionally, luxury art and collectibles have performed strongly in times of economic stress as unrelated stores of value. The metauniverse project will benefit from producing luxury assets and experiences to compete with or collaborate with high art-cult communities in the NFT industry, such as BAYC and individual creators and collectors who build a following around markets such as Art Blocks\",\"t